               <msContents>
                  <summary>ca. 227 x 178 x 95. F<locus target="#1r">fols. 1r, </locus>-2v: Mystagogia. F<locus target="#3r">3r, </locus>-12v: Anaphora of Our Lord. F<locus target="#13r">13r, </locus>-60v: Gospel of John. F<locus target="#61r">61r, </locus>-157v: Harp of Praise. F<locus target="#158r">158r, </locus>-181v: Sword of the Trinity, ዜና፡ ነገሮሙ፡ . F<locus target="#182r">182r, </locus>-196v: Anaphora of Our Lady Mary attributed to Cyriacus of Behensa. F<locus target="#197r">197r, </locus>-203v: Miracles of Mary. F<locus target="#203v">203v, </locus>-205r: Image of Saint Mark, the Evangelist, Chaine Repertoire 198, written in a later hand. F<locus target="#206r">206r</locus>-209v: Asmat prayers of the Archangels. Owner Hayla Maryam is throughout the first part of the book; Owner Gabra Iyasus is mentioned throughout the latter part of the book.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>
                  </msItem>
